-- EEX to Start Spot United Nations Carbon Offset Trading on Dec. 5
-- B y   A l e s s a n d r o   V i t e l l i
-- 2012-11-20T13:27:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/eex-to-start-spot-united-nations-carbon-offset-trading-on-dec-5.html
European Energy Exchange AG will
start trading in spot contracts for United Nations carbon
offsets on Dec. 5.  The Leipzig, Germany-based bourse will offer contracts for
UN offsets eligible in the European Union’s carbon market
through April, as well as UN credits that are eligible in the
third phase of the bloc’s carbon market, which runs from 2012
through 2020, the exchange said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandro Vitelli in London at 
 avitelli1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
